        <div xml:id="AN18-kilavi"></div>
        <div xml:id="AN18">
            <lg type="edition"><l>nīrniṟaṅ karappa vūḻuṟu <choice><seg>putirntu</seg><seg>putirnta</seg></choice></l>
<l><choice><seg>pūmalark</seg><seg>pūmalar</seg></choice> <supplied>kaña</supplied>liya kaṭuvaraṟ kāṉyāṟṟuk</l>
<l>karāan tuñcuṅ kalluyar maṟucuḻi</l>
<l>marāa yāṉai matantapa voṟṟi</l>
<l><supplied>yu</supplied>rā<supplied>a</supplied> vīrkku muṭkuvaru nīttaṅ</l>
<l>kaṭuṅkaṭ paṉṟiyi ṉaṭuṅkātu tuṇintu</l>
<l>nāma <choice><seg>varuntuṟaip</seg><seg>varuntuṇaip</seg></choice> pērtan tiyāmat</l>
<l>tīṅkum varupavō vōṅkal veṟpa</l>
<l>vorunāḷ viḻuma muṟiṉum vaḻināḷ</l>
<l>vāḻkuva ḷallaḷeṉ ṟōḻi yāvatu</l>
<l>mūṟila vaḻikaḷum payila vaḻaṅkunar</l>
<l>nīṭiṉ ṟāka viḻukkuva rataṉā</l>
<l>lulamaral <choice><seg>varutta</seg><seg>varuttamu</seg></choice> muṟutumem paṭappaik</l>
<l>koḻuntē ṉiḻaitta kōṭuyar neṭuvaraip</l>
<l>paḻantūṅku <choice><seg>naḷirppiṟ</seg><seg>naḷippiṟ</seg></choice> kāntaḷam potumpiṟ</l>
<l>pakaṉī variṉum puṇarkuvai yakaṉmalai</l>
<l>vāṅkamaik kaṇṇiṭai kaṭuppayā</l>
<l>yōmpiṉa ḷeṭutta taṭameṉ ṟōḷē.</l></lg>
            <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>Oh man from the high mountain, will they come here too,</l>
<l>the dreadful floods that forcefully drag</l>
<l rend="indent">	an unaccompanied elephant</l>
<l rend="indent">	into repellent whirling high on the stones, where alligators sleep,</l>
<l rend="indent">	in the fast-coming forest river dense with flowering blossoms</l>
<l rend="indent">	dropped off in [their] blown state so as to hide the colour of the water,</l>
<l rend="indent">	pressing [him] down so that [his] strength fails,</l>
<l>with the unwavering resolve of a fierce-eyed hog,</l>
<l>breaking loose from the fearful ghat at midnight?</l>
<l>If one day calamity strikes,</l>
<l>my friend won’t live through the day.</l>
<l>Those who habitually wander ways free from any obstacle</l>
<l>will slip before long.<note place="foot">nīṭu-iṉṟu-āka has to be understood here as a negative adverbial expression.</note></l>
<l rend="indent">	Therefore,</l>
<l>we will suffer perturbing distress.</l>
<l rend="indent">	In our garden,</l>
<l>even if you come by day</l>
<l rend="indent">	to the grove with Malabar lilies, into the hanging coolness of fruit,</l>
<l rend="indent">	on the big mountain high with peaks where rich honey is made,</l>
<l rend="indent">	you will unite</l>
<l>with [her of] soft broad shoulders raised under my mother’s</l>
<l rend="indent">	protection, resembling the joints of bending bamboo</l>
<l rend="indent">	from the wide mountain.</l>
<l rend="indent"></l></lg>
        </div>
    </body>
